title: For Sale/Trade:  Marlin MR7 Bolt Rifle W/ Nice Glass
postcontent: I am listing a rifle out of my collection that you hardly ever see available and most folks aren't familiar with. This is a beautiful 1998 "born on" date Marlin MR7 chambered in 30-06. In almost like new condition with absolutely no flaws, it has a beautiful walnut checkered stock inlaid with the Marlin bullseye, 22" fully floated, crowned and recessed JM stamped barrel, almost flawless bluing, and a jeweled bolt that was masterfully reworked by Skip Baldwin in Michigan. It is topped with a matching set of Leupold rings and bases and a awesome period correct Swift Model 656 3-9x40 scope. Here is a brief history of the rifle, which is touted as one of the finest and most accurate bolt rifles to ever be produced:The Marlin MR-7 was only made from 1996-1999. It was only chambered in .25-06, .270, .280, and .30-06. It features a 3-position safety, a bolt face encircled by three rings of 4140 steel, a shrouded striker and high-visibility cocking indicator. It has an adjustable 3-6 lb. trigger, a forged, machined and heat-treated receiver and an extra-strong bolt lockup. The MR-7 has a hinged floorplate with a removable yet securely mounted 4-shot box magazine (The MR-7B does not). It has a 22" barrel with 6-groove precision rifling and a recessed muzzle. It also has a classically configured, cut-checkered American walnut stock. The later (1999) MR-7B was made with birch wood for the stock and the MR-7B didn't use a floorplate. It was a few $ cheaper and in 1999 the MR-7B was only available in .270 and .30-06 calibers.The Ring of steel around the cartridge and the strong locking lug bolt-face was mimicked off of the Remington 700.The wing-style safety was mimicked from the Winchester Model 70.The "Dogleg" Bolt handle mimicked the Ruger 77The floorplate with the detachable mag was mimicked from the Browning A-Bolt. This would be a special setup for someone's collection or a superb and accurate hunting setup. Asking $800 sale or trade, and I'll consider any nice firearm offers. Thanks for looking!
